This plugin integrates with several community Model Context Protocol (MCP)
servers. Each MCP is an independent third-party project owned by its
respective authors. artysan does not redistribute their binaries; users
install them themselves following the upstream instructions.

  code-review-graph
    Repository: https://github.com/tirth8205/code-review-graph
    Role:       Persistent incremental knowledge graph used by /develop
                (impact_radius warm-up) and /qa (regression scope=impacted,
                affected flows, test coverage).
    Bundling:   Declared in `.mcp.json` so Claude Code auto-starts it when
                this plugin is enabled. Binary itself must be installed by
                the user (`pipx install code-review-graph`).
    Fallback:   /develop and /qa degrade to `tests-only` when the binary
                is unavailable on PATH.

  affine-mcp-server
    Repository: https://github.com/DAWNCR0W/affine-mcp-server
    Role:       Primary documentation storage (AFFiNE Cloud / self-hosted)
                used by /define (PRD authoring) and /ticket (ticket bodies
                referenced from feature pages).
    Bundling:   NOT bundled. Required for /define and /ticket to write to
                AFFiNE; users install + auth separately.
    Fallback:   `setup-config.sh` can fall back to Notion (community MCP)
                or local-only mode (markdown files in `.claude/product/`).

  frame0-mcp-server
    Repository: https://github.com/niklauslee/frame0-mcp-server
    Role:       Wireframe authoring (shapes, pages, export PNG) used by
                /wireframe.
    Bundling:   NOT bundled. Optional — required only when running
                /wireframe; install separately.

  playwright-mcp
    Repository: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright-mcp
    Role:       Headless browser navigation + screenshot used by /qa
                step-01-collect for wireframe drift detection.
    Bundling:   NOT bundled. Optional — required only when
                `qa.wireframe_check.enabled=true` in `artysan.config.json`;
                install separately.

